2. cs.SI (Signal Processing) - The paper focuses on signal processing techniques for wideband spectrum sensing, which falls under the scope of cs.SI. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a practical solution for wideband spectrum sensing, which involves designing a system for real-time implementation. This falls under the scope of cs.SY. 
4. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - Wideband spectrum sensing is an important component of cognitive radio networks, which falls under the scope of cs.NI. 
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - Although the paper does not explicitly mention machine learning, compressed sensing is a technique that has been widely used in machine learning applications.
